    "content_hash": "1703c5ce3ac7c865",
    "department": "Product Management",
    "description": "At Snowflake, we are powering the era of the agentic enterprise. To usher in this new era, we seek AI-native thinkers across every function who are energized by the opportunity to reinvent how they work. You don’t just use tools; you possess an innate curiosity, treating AI as a high-trust collaborator that is core to how you solve problems and accelerate your impact. We look for low-ego individuals who thrive in dynamic and fast-moving environments and move with an experimental mindset — who rapidly test emerging capabilities to discover simpler, more powerful ways to deliver results. At Snowflake, your role isn't just to execute a function, but to help redefine the future of how work gets done.\n\nSnowflake’s AI Data Cloud is the unified platform and connected ecosystem of organizations building, using, and sharing data, apps, and AI. At the foundation of this platform is trust. Customers rely on Snowflake to run their most mission critical data and AI workloads with confidence across regions, clouds, and failure scenarios.\n\nReplication and disaster recovery are core to that trust. As Snowflake powers increasingly always on enterprise AI and data workloads, we are investing in maturing our replication and DR capabilities to be more reliable, observable, and easy to operate at global scale.\n\nWe are seeking a Product Manager to help drive execution across Snowflake’s replication and disaster recovery roadmap. This role is ideal for an early career PM who wants to work on foundational cloud infrastructure in the AI era, learn how large scale distributed systems are built, and develop strong product instincts through close partnership with senior PMs, architects, and engineering leaders.\n\n\nIN THIS ROLE, YOU WILL\n\n - Own end to end delivery of specific replication and disaster recovery features, from problem definition through launch and iteration\n\n - Execute on Snowflake’s BCDR roadmap, including replication coverage expansion, managed DR workflows, auditing, and observability\n\n - Use data, metrics, and AI assisted analysis to identify gaps, prioritize work, and measure impact across replication and DR workflows\n\n - Partner closely with engineering teams to translate customer, business, and platform needs into clear product requirements and execution plans\n\n - Develop product judgment around reliability tradeoffs, consistency, and SLAs in large scale distributed systems\n\n - Coordinate with adjacent teams across storage, metadata, security, and GTM to ensure clean platform integration\n\n - Participate in customer conversations, previews, and feedback loops with enterprise customers running mission critical AI and data workloads\n\n - Leverage modern AI and analytics tools to accelerate product discovery, documentation, and decision making\n\n\nOUR IDEAL CANDIDATE HAS\n\n - Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science from a top tier undergraduate program\n\n - 5+ years of experience with a background in Product Management, investment banking, or top tier management consulting\n\n - Strong analytical and problem solving skills, with comfort using data to inform product decisions\n\n - Interest in cloud infrastructure, distributed systems, and platforms that power enterprise AI and data workloads\n\n - Comfort using AI tools to improve productivity, insight generation, and execution.\n\n - Excellent written and verbal communication skills\n\n - A growth mindset and eagerness to learn from senior PMs and engineers\n   \n\n\nWHY JOIN THIS TEAM?\n\nThis role offers a rare opportunity to work on core platform infrastructure that powers the most mission critical AI and data workloads at the world’s largest enterprises early in your product career. You will gain hands on experience building replication and disaster recovery capabilities at global scale, develop fluency in using data and AI as core product management tools, and be mentored by senior product and engineering leaders shaping Snowflake’s platform.\n\nEvery Snowflake employee is expected to follow the company’s confidentiality and security standards for handling sensitive data. Snowflake employees must abide by the company’s data security plan as an essential part of their duties. It is every employee's duty to keep customer information secure and confidential.\n\nSnowflake is growing fast, and we’re scaling our team to help enable and accelerate our growth. We are looking for people who share our values, challenge ordinary thinking, and push the pace of innovation while building a future for themselves and Snowflake.\n\nHow do you want to make your impact?\n\nFor jobs located in the United States, please visit the job posting on the Snowflake Careers Site for salary and benefits information: careers.snowflake.com http://careers.snowflake.com",
